      "span_text": "Moreover, another study investigating the effects of 5,7-dihydroxy-8-nitrochrysin (NOChR) on apoptosis in human gastric carcinoma cell line, SGC-7901, showed that NOChR markedly inhibited the proliferation of SGC-7901 cells in a dose-dependent manner, where the potency of NOChR (IC 50 of 4.14 μmol/L) was 10 times higher than that of unmodified chrysin (IC 50 of 40.56-μmol/L)"
